<item>
            <title>[LU-8593] sanity-lfsck test_19b: (3) Expected 1 repaired, but got 0</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8593</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Saurabh Tandan &amp;lt;saurabh.tandan@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/970188da-723b-11e6-8a8c-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/970188da-723b-11e6-8a8c-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_19b failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;(3) Expected 1 repaired, but got 0
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test config:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== sanity-lfsck test 19b: OST-object inconsistency self repair ======================================= 22:01:02 (1472878862)
Inject failure stub to make the OST-object to back point to
non-exist MDT-object
CMD: onyx-43vm8 /usr/sbin/lctl set_param fail_loc=0x1611
fail_loc=0x1611
error: set_param: setting /proc/fs/lustre/ldlm/namespaces/lustre-OST0000-osc-ffff88007a7f1800/lru_size=clear: Invalid argument
ldlm.namespaces.lustre-OST0000-osc-ffff88007a7f1800.lock_unused_count=1
CMD: onyx-43vm8 /usr/sbin/lctl set_param fail_loc=0
fail_loc=0
Nothing should be fixed since self detect and repair is disabled
CMD: onyx-43vm8 /usr/sbin/lctl get_param -n obdfilter.lustre-OST0000.lfsck_verify_pfid
Read RPC with right parent FID should be accepted,
and cause parent FID on OST to be fixed
CMD: onyx-43vm8 /usr/sbin/lctl set_param -n obdfilter.lustre-OST0000.lfsck_verify_pfid 1
foo
CMD: onyx-43vm8 /usr/sbin/lctl get_param -n obdfilter.lustre-OST0000.lfsck_verify_pfid
 sanity-lfsck test_19b: @@@@@@ FAIL: (3) Expected 1 repaired, but got 0
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Might be related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5030&quot; title=&quot;&amp;quot;lctl {get,set}_param&amp;quot; should also check in /sys/fs/{lnet,lustre}&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5030&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5030&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>EL7.2 Server/SLES12 SP1 Client&lt;br/&gt;
master, build# 3431</environment>
